When attaching a file or screenshot to an issue, you also have the ability to add a comment. Those comments appear at the bottom and don't contain a link pointing to the file associated with the comment. 

If multiple comments and attachments are added within the same day, often times you are left to match up times and guess which attachment is being talked about.

It would be nice to have an option to add a link to the attachment in the comment when a file is attached to an issue.

*Workaround*

An option would be to *display* the attachment in the comment. For example, when adding a comment to an issue with an attachment named "test.png", you can add to your comment the following wiki markup code:

{noformat}
!test.png!
{noformat}

